HEADWORD: Transshipment
<hw>Trans*ship"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
transshipping, or transferring, as goods, from one ship or conveyance to
another.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>transhipment</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

